A function declaration tells the compiler about a function's name, return type, and parameters.
what is function declaration?
     It tells the compiler about a function name and how to call a function
what is the function's name?
     Actual name of the function
what is return type?
     specifies the output of the function
what are paramaters?
     it is used to refer the variable
Function declaration is required when you define a function in one source file and you call that function in another file.
